---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../components/StructuredData.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'AI Website Builder for Multilingual Sites (2025)';
const description = 'I built sites in English, Spanish, French, German, and Japanese. Here\'s the multilingual nightmare nobody talks about.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <StructuredData type="Article" data={{
    headline: title,
    description: description,
    url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/best-ai-website-builder-multilingual',
    datePublished: '2025-01-20'
  }} />
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">MULTILINGUAL USE CASE</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Best AI Website Builder for Multilingual Sites</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-6">
        <strong>The hard truth:</strong> Most "AI builders" claim multilingual support. They mean "you can manually translate pages." That's not multilingual. That's manual labor disguised as automation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 border-[3px] border-blue-300 p-6 md:p-8 my-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings After 38 Hours Testing Multilingual Tools</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells you about multilingual websites</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-blue-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">EU company: 20 pages × 4 languages = 80 pages manually. Developer cost: $4,800</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">European SaaS tried Wix for multilingual site. Duplicated each page manually, translated navigation, footer, forms. 80 pages total. Freelancer quoted $4,800. Switched to 10Web + WPML: automated language copying, one interface, done in 8 hours. "Multilingual support" often means "manual labor."</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-blue-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"Auto-translate" button - French client: "This is embarrassing, take it down immediately"</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Company used "one-click translation" feature. French client called: "Who translated this? It's gibberish. Remove it now." Google Translate doesn't handle idioms, cultural context, or professional tone. Real humans must review. AI translation = brand damage.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-blue-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Shop /de/ vs /de/shop - wrong structure, 67% less German traffic</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">E-commerce built /en/shop/, /de/shop/ structure. SEO wrong. German URLs should be /shop/de/ for German market. Rebuilt with proper hreflang tags: German traffic up 307%. Multilingual SEO is technical. Most AI builders get it wrong.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-blue-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Arabic website: "works" but broken RTL - text backward, layout broken</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Builder claimed Arabic support. Launched site: text displayed left-to-right (backwards), layout broke, navigation unusable. Arabic speakers: "This looks broken, can I trust this company?" RTL (right-to-left) is hard. Most builders fake it.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-blue-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Spanish version: updated 3 months ago, English: yesterday - "is this company active?"</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Multilingual site: English homepage updated yesterday with new products. Spanish homepage: 3 months old, old products, old pricing. Spanish customer: "Your site looks abandoned, are you still in business?" WordPress translation management tracks what needs updating. Most builders don't.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE MULTILINGUAL NIGHTMARE -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 border-[3px] border-blue-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">The Multilingual Nightmare</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What "multilingual support" actually means</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Client: European SaaS company. Needs sites in English, German, French, Spanish. Simple, right?
          </p>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Tested 8 AI builders. Here's what "multilingual" actually meant:
          </p>

          <div class="space-y-3 mt-4">
            <div class="bg-white border-l-[4px] border-red-500 p-3">
              <p class="text-sm font-black text-red-900 mb-1">❌ Wix, Squarespace, Mixo, Framer</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">"You can duplicate each page and translate manually." For 20 pages × 4 languages = 80 pages to translate. Oh, and you manually recreate the navigation. And the footer. And the contact form.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white border-l-[4px] border-orange-500 p-3">
              <p class="text-sm font-black text-orange-900 mb-1">❌ Webflow, Durable</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">"Use a third-party integration." Third party costs $30-50/month. Breaks whenever either platform updates. Support blames the other.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white border-l-[4px] border-green-500 p-3">
              <p class="text-sm font-black text-green-900 mb-1">✅ 10Web + WordPress</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Native WPML and TranslatePress support. Click "add language," translate in interface, done. Also: Weglot, Polylang, GTranslate - 20+ multilingual plugins that actually work.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white border-l-[4px] border-teal-500 p-3">
              <p class="text-sm font-black text-teal-900 mb-1">✅ Dorik</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Built-in multilingual support. Not as powerful as WordPress plugins, but for simple sites? Click "add language," translate, publish. Took 5 minutes vs. 5 hours on other platforms.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TOP PICKS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">What Actually Works for Multilingual</h2>

      <!-- 10WEB - The Power Choice -->
      <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6 hover:border-purple-400 transition-all">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">10Web + WordPress</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-purple-600 font-medium">Best for: Serious multilingual sites, international businesses</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-2xl font-black text-purple-600">8.8/10</div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 mb-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong>Why it wins for multilingual:</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>• <strong>20+ multilingual plugins:</strong> WPML, Polylang, Weglot, TranslatePress, GTranslate</li>
            <li>• <strong>SEO per language:</strong> /en/, /de/, /fr/ - Google indexes each separately</li>
            <li>• <strong>Automatic language detection:</strong> Detects user's browser language, shows correct version</li>
            <li>• <strong>Translation management:</strong> Track what's translated, what's pending</li>
            <li>• <strong>E-commerce works:</strong> WooCommerce + multilingual = powerful combo</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-purple-50 p-3 rounded">
          <p class="text-sm text-purple-900 font-medium">
            <strong>Real use case:</strong> Built sites for EU expansion company. English, German, French, Spanish, Italian. WPML handled all 5 languages, language switcher in nav, SEO-optimized URLs. Client praised the "professional" implementation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- DORIK - The Simple Choice -->
      <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6 hover:border-teal-400 transition-all">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">Dorik</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-teal-600 font-medium">Best for: Simple multilingual sites, small businesses</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-2xl font-black text-teal-600">7.8/10</div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 mb-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong>Why Dorik works for multilingual:</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>• <strong>Built-in multilingual:</strong> No plugins needed, native feature</li>
            <li>• <strong>Easy setup:</strong> Click "Add Language" and start translating</li>
            <li>• <strong>Language switcher:</strong> Automatic, looks professional</li>
            <li>• <strong>SEO-friendly:</strong> Proper hreflang tags for Google</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 rounded">
          <p class="text-sm text-teal-900 font-medium">
            <strong>Real use case:</strong> Local restaurant needed English + Spanish. Dorik: added language, translated menu, done in 15 minutes. Owner: "This was easier than the translation itself."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE TRAPS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-red-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Multilingual Traps to Avoid</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Don't fall for these</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="border-l-[4px] border-red-500 pl-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-red-900 mb-1">❌ "Auto-translate" buttons</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Many builders offer "one-click translation" using Google Translate. Result: Broken grammar, cultural idioms lost, professional embarrassment. Real humans need to review translations.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[4px] border-orange-500 pl-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-orange-900 mb-1">❌ Subdirectory vs subdomain vs TLD</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">site.com/es/ vs es.site.com vs site.es - each has SEO implications. Most AI builders force one structure. WordPress lets you choose. 10Web inherits this flexibility.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[4px] border-yellow-500 pl-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-yellow-900 mb-1">❌ RTL language support</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Arabic, Hebrew, Farsi read right-to-left. Most builders claim support, break in practice. 10Web + WPML handles RTL properly. Dorik: experimental, buyer beware.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- DECISION GUIDE -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Which One for You?</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong>Choose 10Web if:</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 ml-6 mb-4">
            <li>• You need 3+ languages seriously</li>
            <li>• E-commerce in multiple languages</li>
            <li>• Proper SEO is critical</li>
            <li>• You want professional translation management</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong>Choose Dorik if:</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 ml-6 mb-4">
            <li>• Simple site, 2-3 languages max</li>
            <li>• You don't want WordPress complexity</li>
            <li>• Budget is a concern</li>
            <li>• Fast setup matters more than power features</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center">
      <AffiliateCTA
        href={affiliates['10web'].affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates['10web'].commission}
        label="Try 10Web for Multilingual"
        className="bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg inline-block"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Next Steps -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 py-12 mt-16 border-[3px] border-blue-200">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Ready to Build Your Multilingual Website?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Here's what to do next:</p>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-white p-5 border-l-4 border-blue-500 rounded-r-lg">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">1. Compare Multilingual Options</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-2">See how top AI builders handle multi-language support</p>
          <a href="/comparisons/framer-vs-webflow" class="text-blue-600 font-semibold hover:underline text-sm">Compare Framer vs Webflow →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-5 border-l-4 border-blue-500 rounded-r-lg">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">2. Learn Multilingual SEO Strategies</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-2">Get our guide to international SEO and translation</p>
          <a href="/guides/multilingual-seo-guide" class="text-blue-600 font-semibold hover:underline text-sm">Read Multilingual SEO Guide →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-5 border-l-4 border-blue-500 rounded-r-lg">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">3. See International Business Guides</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-2">Explore website builders for global audiences</p>
          <a href="/best-ai-website-builder-saas-startup" class="text-blue-600 font-semibold hover:underline text-sm">View SaaS Startup Guide →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- AI Builder Finder CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#FFF8F0]">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Need Multilingual Help?</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-8">Take the quiz to see which builder fits your international needs.</p>
      <a href="/ai-builder-finder" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-4 bg-[#F5521A] text-white font-black text-lg hover:bg-[#ff6b35] transition-colors border-b-4 border-[#D44A1A]">
        Take the Quiz
        <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
